  "text": "In this section, we address several cases left open by Mattei et al. [CITATION_1] . They showed that the unweighted bribery problem is solvable in polynomial time for the one-step voting systems OP , OV , OK * for several cost schemes. For the cost scheme C ANY and all bribery actions, and for the cost scheme C LEVEL with bribery actions DV and I V + DV , the computational complexity was still open. In this section, we show that all of these problems are polynomially tractable as well, thus completing the complexity table for OP , OV , OK * in the unweighted case. An overview of all results (both from Mattei et al. [CITATION_2] and ours) can be found in Table 2 at the end of this work.",
